-- Commercial Bank of Qatar launches $750 mln bond, pricing at tight end
-- By Archana Narayanan
-- Tue Jun 17, 2014 08:48AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, June 17 (Reuters) - Commercial Bank of Qatar <COMB.QA> has launched a $750 million, five-year bond offer that will price later on Tuesday, with pricing at the tight end of guidance because of strong investor demand.

The transaction is set to price at a spread of 117 basis points over mid-swaps, a document from lead managers said, at the tight end of a revised range of 117-120 bps over the same benchmark given earlier on Tuesday. [ID:nL5N0OY269] Pricing was revised twice on Tuesday, with initial guidance given as in the area of 135 bps before it was changed to 120-125 bps over the benchmark. Investor orders worth more than $3 billion have been placed for the transaction, an earlier update from lead managers said.